": "Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2018-08-23T19:26:37Z", "updated_at": "2019-08-10T11:02:28Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It's not clear why `std::io::lazy` doesn't use `Once`, as that was available at the time when it was introduced.\r\n\r\n#53108 marked `Lazy::new` as `unsafe` because of the lack of reentrance safety in the mutex being used, but `Once` *specifically doesn't* have reentrancy issues.\r\n\r\n`lazy_static` version: https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/lazy-static.rs/blob/13159c2b615903d93b4cd4f98d17fdfe70392a3a/src/inline_lazy.rs\r\n\r\nHowever, we need to change it per https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/lazy-static.rs/issues/117, otherwise it's **unsound**.\r\n\r\ncc @RalfJung @alexcrichton ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/53646/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/53646/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}